    "name": "Yomp for Zhi",
    "steam_appid": 3062980,
    "required_age": 0,
    "is_free": false,
    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Yomp for Zhi is a difficult turn-based RPG about a journey across Holtoss (a region riddled with crime and dangerous creatures). The unlikely heroes have a limited amount of days to rescue people who are going to be killed (including the titular Zhi).</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >No backtracking.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >No getting lost.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >0 HP means a character is dead for good.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Fast paced with no long animations.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Brutal long lasting injuries/ailments.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >41 different characters to hire along the way (and 2 secret non-canon ones).</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >150+ enemy types!</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >6 unlockable difficulties and 2 unlockable bonus modes.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Most enemies can become temporary allies (referred to as Homies).</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Dozens of enemy factions so enemies can often be seen attacking each other.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Weather conditions (including fog that can obscure the identities of enemies)</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Under certain circumstances, enemies can return for revenge if they aren't killed.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The overworld often has an overwhelming amount of choice (hunting, shopping, selling, stealing, gambling, combining items, working, panhandling, fishing, etc.)</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><u><strong>Things to note:</strong></u></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The game can be run using Vulkan renderer or OpenGL3.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >A mouse is highly recommended over using a laptop touchpad.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >No controller support.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >A successful run usually takes around 1-4 hours. <u>There's a &quot;Save &amp; Quit&quot; feature so you can resume a run later, but loading it will discard the saved run.</u></p></li></ul>",
